# A simple AND gate specification.
# This demonstrates Tau's stream processing capabilities for digital logic.

# Define two input streams and one output stream from the console.
# In a real application, these could be mapped to files or other I/O.
tau i1 = console
tau i2 = console
tau o1 = console

# Define the logical relationship for the AND gate.
# The output stream o1 at time t is the logical AND of the input streams i1 and i2 at time t.
o1[t] = i1[t] && i2[t]
